TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Principle of Minimum Differentiation Holds under Sufficient Heterogeneity
AU  - de Palma, A.
AU  - Ginsburgh, V.
AU  - Papageorgiou, Y. Y.
AU  - J.-F. Thisse
AB  - [The so-called Principle of Minimum Differentiation, stated by Hotelling, has been challenged by many authors. This paper restores the Principle by showing that n firms locate at the center of the market and charge prices higher than the marginal cost of production when heterogeneity in consumers' tastes is "large enough."]
